{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place olive oil, 1 Tbsp lemon juice and salt in mixing bowl and mix <nobr>3 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr> to make a marinade.","Place prawns in a bowl and coat with 2 Tbsp marinade. Allow to rest for 10 minutes while preparing the soup.","Add onions and garlic to remaining marinade in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Sauté <nobr>2 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add cucumbers and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then sauté <nobr>6 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, thread prawns alternately with quartered lemon slices onto 6 wooden skewers and arrange them in Varoma dish.","Add water, vegetable stock paste, black pepper and remaining marinade from prawns to mixing bowl, set Varoma in position and cook <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Set Varoma aside.","Add milk, flour and remaining 1 Tbsp lemon juice to mixing bowl, insert measuring cup and blend <strong><nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>-9, increasing speed gradually.<\/strong> Remove measuring cup, set Varoma back in position and cook <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Set Varoma aside.","Add dill (if using) to mixing bowl, season to taste and blend until frothy <strong><nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>-9, increasing speed gradually.<\/strong> Pour soup into 6 bowls, place a prawn skewer on top of each bowl and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["40 g olive oil","2 Tbsp lemon juice","½ tsp salt","24 large raw prawns, peeled and deveined","80 g onions, quartered","2 garlic cloves","500 g cucumbers, unpeeled, cut in pieces","1 lemon, cut in round slices, then quartered","500 g water","1 heaped tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade","¼ tsp ground black pepper","200 g milk","40 g plain flour","2 Tbsp fresh dill, chopped (optional)"]}],"id":"r150890","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-xyBecIlXRfs\/XZMz2nsnreI\/AAAAAAAAa2E\/17xh_d1-cLodfEjkKwmAOwz8cc9Euqm6gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lUTqZktuG95Ivpq0.png","title":"Cucumber Soup with Prawn Skewers","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"12 g","fat":"9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"10 g","calories":"733 kJ \/ 175 kcal"},"usefulItems":"wooden skewers","hintsAndTricks":["If using frozen prawns, defrost before marinating.<br>- Unpeeled cucumbers give more colour and flavour to the soup.<br>- Long skewers can be cut to fit the Varoma dish.<br>- In hot weather this soup can be served chilled. For a fresh summer flavour, replace dill with fresh mint or coriander.","<i>Cucumber makes a really refreshing soup. For a creamy white soup, peel the cucumbers and for a pale green soup, leave the skin on. Either way is perfect when you have a bumper crop in the garden! The prawn skewers add a touch of elegance and complement the flavour of the soup.<\/i>","Instead of flour use <nobr>150 g cooked<\/nobr> potatoes, cut in pieces, to thicken the soup.<br>- Use cream instead of milk, or half cream, half milk.<br>- For vegetarian skewers, replace lemon slices with cherry tomatoes and prawns with one or several of the following: small mushrooms <nobr>(Ø 3 cm),<\/nobr> feta cheese cubes, or tofu cubes marinated in soy sauce.<br>- The soup can also be seasoned with a splash of dry white wine."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","35m","6 portions"]}